Program 4: Operator Overloading
Aim: To demonstrate operator overloading in C++ for adding two complex numbers using the + operator.

Algorithm:

Start the program.
Define a class Complex.
Overload the + operator.
Create objects and add them.
Display the result.
Stop the program.
Source Code:

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Complex {
    float real, imag;

public:
    Complex(float r = 0, float i = 0) {
        real = r;
        imag = i;
    }

    Complex operator + (Complex c) {
        Complex temp;
        temp.real = real + c.real;
        temp.imag = imag + c.imag;
        return temp;
    }

    void display() {
        cout << real << " + " << imag << "i" << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Complex c1(3.5, 2.5), c2(1.5, 4.5), c3;
    c3 = c1 + c2;
    cout << "Result of addition: ";
    c3.display();
    return 0;
}
Result:

Result of addition: 5 + 7i
